_meanings:
{@--1@} ({%a%}) To say,
speak, tell (with <ab>acc.</ab>, rarely with
<ab>dat.</ab>); {#sA taTyamevABihitA Bavena#}  
<ls>Ku. 3. 63</ls>; <ls>Ms. 1. 42</ls>; <ls>Bk. 7. 78</ls>;  
<ls>Bg. 18. 68.</ls> ({%b%}) To denote, express or 
convey directly or primarily (as sense
&c.); state, mention, set forth;  
{#sAkzAtsaMketitaM yorTamaBiDatte sa vAcakaH#} <ls>K. P. 2</ls>;
{#tannAma yenABidaDAti sattvaM#}. ({%c%}) To speak
or say to, address.

{@--2@} To name, call,
designate; usually in {%<ab>pass.</ab>%} ({#--DIyate#});
{#idaM SarIraM kOMteya kzetramityaBiDIyate#}  
<ls>Bg. 13. 1.</ls>
